                            <comment id="52224" author="utopiabound" created="Tue, 12 Feb 2013 12:14:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That looks more like what I would use; It&apos;s like a description list from LaTeX (which is my typesetting language of choice).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="52219" author="rhenwood" created="Tue, 12 Feb 2013 11:33:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed - the list doesn&apos;t looks as good without bold.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You&apos;ve prompted me to look further around the Docbook schema... I&apos;m reviewing &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.docbook.org/tdg/en/html/variablelist.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.docbook.org/tdg/en/html/variablelist.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;which maybe the correct solution (rather than just removing &apos;style=bold&apos;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;



&lt;p&gt;What are your thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="52153" author="utopiabound" created="Mon, 11 Feb 2013 14:54:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just removing the &apos;style=bold&apos; does cause those items without it to look different (not bold).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
